title: Switch port synchronization
agents: special
catalog: hw/network
license: MIT
distribution: DanielDietz-de
description:
 Compares the operational state of one-to-one interface services on two Checkmk
 hosts. Interface services are sourced from Livestatus, so the check reuses the
 existing Checkmk interface discovery and does not perform another SNMP poll.

 A port service is discovered when at least one corresponding member is up at
 discovery. This catches an asymmetric pair immediately while excluding ports
 that are down on both switches and normally unused. An accepted port service
 is OK only when both interfaces are confirmed up. One down or both down results
 in CRIT. Missing, stale, or unparseable source data results in UNKNOWN.

inventory:
 One pair-status service is always discovered. One additional service is
 discovered for every one-to-one interface item for which at least one member
 is confirmed up during service discovery.
